00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:19.560
You see the expression of CD36 on the x-axis, so you're getting a major increase

193
00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:23.200
in CD36 lipid receptor expression.

194
00:11:23.520 --> 00:11:27.300
They also have high levels of PD-L1 and CSF1R, so really bad

195
00:11:27.380 --> 00:11:31.080
macrophages. And indeed, when we went back to our mouse model, we could

196
00:11:31.140 --> 00:11:32.020
identify

197
00:11:33.040 --> 00:11:36.280
more characteristics of these lipid macrophages.

198
00:11:36.700 --> 00:11:40.280
So this is this P53 BRCA-deficient breast

199
00:11:40.360 --> 00:11:43.040
cancer model. Again, these are immunocompetent mice.

200
00:11:43.400 --> 00:11:45.650
You treat the mice with olaparib for five days.

201
00:11:45.700 --> 00:11:48.320
You have a bit of a decrease in tumor volume.

202
00:11:48.360 --> 00:11:51.900
When you look just at the macrophages, these

203
00:11:51.940 --> 00:11:55.700
macrophages after olaparib treatment express PD-L1, the lipid uptake

204
00:11:55.760 --> 00:11:59.600
receptor CD36, CSF1R, TREM2, and other

205
00:11:59.720 --> 00:12:03.220
markers suggesting suppressive

206
00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:07.164
phenotype.So, at the same time we were

207
00:12:07.204 --> 00:12:10.884
identifying these really suppressive macrophages, we were making another

208
00:12:11.224 --> 00:12:14.884
discovery, along with several others at that time, which

