00:35:25.404 --> 00:35:28.264
Okay. So I'm going to talk a little bit about our mental model here.

627
00:35:28.304 --> 00:35:32.244
And our view is that immunosuppressive myeloid cells are a top target to

628
00:35:32.304 --> 00:35:35.384
make immunotherapies more effective for our brain tumor patients and solid tumor

629
00:35:35.424 --> 00:35:39.024
patients. That single cell genomics combined with patient tumor organoids are a

630
00:35:39.064 --> 00:35:42.624
really powerful platform for both therapy discovery and translation.

631
00:35:43.664 --> 00:35:46.154
And I'm going to spend some time on this, that we should move beyond Louvain and

632
00:35:46.204 --> 00:35:49.444
Lighting clustering, which is typically projected on a UMAP, to understand our

633
00:35:49.484 --> 00:35:53.344
single cell RNA sequencing data. Because complicated cells like myeloid

634
00:35:53.364 --> 00:35:56.744
cells and cancer cells that exist on a spectrum are really challenging to

635
00:35:56.764 --> 00:35:58.364
understand with clustering in UMAP.

636
00:35:58.804 --> 00:36:01.804
So Louvain and Lighting clustering are reasonably good at identifying cell types,

637
00:36:02.244 --> 00:36:04.544
but pretty poor at pulling out cell activities.

638
00:36:05.184 --> 00:36:08.884
And I would argue that most immunotherapies, and actually most of

639
00:36:08.904 --> 00:36:11.914
our other therapies, aim to target cell activities.

640
00:36:12.744 --> 00:36:16.424
And if you can isolate out the cell activity from the identity, it really

641
00:36:16.444 --> 00:36:19.992
enables a lot of novel insights and new targets.And

642
00:36:20.072 --> 00:36:23.952
so we are now thinking about we should reprogram or remove specific myeloid

643
00:36:23.992 --> 00:36:25.632
cell populations, as Jen talked about,

644
00:36:26.652 --> 00:36:30.532
and the activities of those combined with CAR T cell therapy to make more

645
00:36:30.572 --> 00:36:32.172
persistent responses for our patients.

646
00:36:33.552 --> 00:36:34.732
So I'm going to spend a little bit of time on this.

647
00:36:35.052 --> 00:36:38.612
So Louvain lighting clustering really groups cells based on similarities in gene

648
00:36:38.652 --> 00:36:41.612
expression profile. Every cell is treated as a singular unit.

649
00:36:41.692 --> 00:36:43.332
You put it next to its nearest neighbor on a plot.

650
00:36:43.372 --> 00:36:47.332
You draw a circle around it, make it a cluster, and then all of your gene

651
00:36:47.432 --> 00:36:48.862
sets, your signatures, whatever you call them,

652
00:36:49.762 --> 00:36:53.572
are derived from looking at all the genes expressed in one

653
00:36:53.612 --> 00:36:56.032
cluster compared to all the other clusters.

654
00:36:56.092 --> 00:36:59.932
Oppose that to CNMF, consensus non-negative matrix factorization, which is what we

655
00:37:00.012 --> 00:37:00.192
use,

656
00:37:01.012 --> 00:37:03.982
aims to decompose that single cell RNA sequencing data down into distinct gene

657
00:37:04.012 --> 00:37:07.902
expression programs. So it looks at sets of genes that go up

658
00:37:07.912 --> 00:37:10.312
and down together across thousands of single cells.

659
00:37:10.352 --> 00:37:13.152
Those highly correlated sets of genes, we call programs.

660
00:37:13.592 --> 00:37:16.772
Those programs can be identity program. What cell type is it?

661
00:37:16.892 --> 00:37:20.562
Macrophage, monocyte, dendritic cell, or it can be an activity

662
00:37:20.612 --> 00:37:22.032
program. What is that cell doing?

663
00:37:23.232 --> 00:37:26.252
And importantly, you can have more than one program per cell.

664
00:37:26.332 --> 00:37:30.312
So it allows you to have sort of this matrix, where some of the programs will

665
00:37:30.322 --> 00:37:34.292
define, hey, that cell is a microglia, and other programs say, hey, that

666
00:37:34.352 --> 00:37:38.252
microglia is inflammatory, or that microglia is responding

667
00:37:38.292 --> 00:37:38.972
to interferon.

668
00:37:41.152 --> 00:37:44.452
And so we did this across a large panel of myeloid cells.

669
00:37:44.552 --> 00:37:47.092
In glioma, we pulled out 14 programs.

