00:37:54.932 --> 00:37:58.442
Five of those activity programs were sort of classic response,

674
00:37:58.492 --> 00:38:00.902
hypoxia response, interferon response, cycling programs.

675
00:38:01.552 --> 00:38:04.762
But four of them looked immunomodulatory, whether they were

676
00:38:04.812 --> 00:38:06.912
inflammatory or immunosuppressive.

677
00:38:07.432 --> 00:38:11.282
And if you looked at the programs being used by all the myeloid cells in a

678
00:38:11.312 --> 00:38:14.052
tumor, it were these four programs that were utilized the most.

679
00:38:14.112 --> 00:38:18.012
In fact, 90 plus percent of all of the myeloid cells in a

680
00:38:18.032 --> 00:38:20.152
brain tumor used one of these four programs.

681
00:38:21.932 --> 00:38:23.752
And what's interesting here, this is a very simple plot.

682
00:38:23.792 --> 00:38:27.162
It just says, what are the percent of microglia that express these different

683
00:38:27.232 --> 00:38:30.872
activity programs? And so any given microglia might express one

684
00:38:30.932 --> 00:38:33.752
of two or three different activity programs.

685
00:38:34.332 --> 00:38:37.962
What was really interesting was that these activity programs were

686
00:38:38.152 --> 00:38:39.771
shared across the different cell types.

687
00:38:40.292 --> 00:38:44.072
So for example, this one systemic inflammatory program could be expressed

688
00:38:44.112 --> 00:38:47.942
by all five different cell types. This is very different than what we typically do,

689
00:38:47.952 --> 00:38:51.892
where you take microglia, for example, and then you try to subdivide the

690
00:38:51.932 --> 00:38:55.792
microglia down into inflammatory, immunosuppressive, or interferon responding.

