00:39:05.192 --> 00:39:08.882
You just have to pull them out independently, and then you just apply them to that.

695
00:39:08.892 --> 00:39:12.642
And so that allows you then to think about what is that particular

696
00:39:12.732 --> 00:39:15.262
program? How is it being used across the population of all myeloid cells?

697
00:39:16.492 --> 00:39:19.392
So this is an example of that. This is a really nice data set from Houston

698
00:39:19.432 --> 00:39:23.112
Methodist that we use. So this was their UMAP and their

699
00:39:23.192 --> 00:39:23.672
clustering,

700
00:39:25.192 --> 00:39:27.492
and they basically annotated all of their cells.

701
00:39:27.532 --> 00:39:31.112
So they annotated this cluster as inflammatory microglia, for

702
00:39:31.172 --> 00:39:34.572
example. So we took all of their single cells.

703
00:39:34.792 --> 00:39:37.752
We looked at our programs in their single cells.

704
00:39:38.492 --> 00:39:42.312
And it's true that all the cells that were in their microglia cluster

705
00:39:42.612 --> 00:39:45.132
looked like they were expressing our microglia identity program.

706
00:39:46.212 --> 00:39:49.672
But they also could express one of three different activity programs.

707
00:39:49.712 --> 00:39:53.432
So it was a combination of different sort of cell states that were in that one

708
00:39:53.512 --> 00:39:53.892
cluster.

709
00:39:55.052 --> 00:39:57.852
So what we're really pulling out here is the principal components of myeloid cell

710
00:39:57.912 --> 00:40:01.672
expression phenotypes. And this really brings it home, I think.

711
00:40:01.732 --> 00:40:03.612
Again, UMAPs are good at pulling out cell types.

712
00:40:03.912 --> 00:40:07.422
It's pretty good at pulling out all the microglia clusters and macrophages and

713
00:40:07.452 --> 00:40:09.632
monocytes, which you can do on UMAPs.

714
00:40:10.002 --> 00:40:13.052
But it's really poor at pulling out these cell activities because they're expressed

715
00:40:13.072 --> 00:40:16.912
across multiple clusters. Like this microgli inflammatory program is expressed

716
00:40:16.932 --> 00:40:18.382
across four or five different clusters.

717
00:40:18.772 --> 00:40:22.052
And so you can never pull it out if you're taking one cluster versus all others.

718
00:40:22.162 --> 00:40:23.552
It just gets lost in the background.

719
00:40:25.512 --> 00:40:29.292
Okay, so we basically looked at all of these with a bunch of clinical correlates,

720
00:40:29.332 --> 00:40:32.572
and it were these four programs that were associated with survival and response to

721
00:40:32.612 --> 00:40:35.092
immunotherapy and all the other things. And I'll show you a little bit of that.

722
00:40:35.572 --> 00:40:39.552
And so these four programs are now how we think how we should define these

723
00:40:39.592 --> 00:40:43.212
myeloid cells. And again, so you have these two inflammatory

724
00:40:43.292 --> 00:40:46.972
programs. A systemic inflammatory program is like the default inflammatory

725
00:40:47.052 --> 00:40:48.852
program for monocytes and all over the body.

726
00:40:48.892 --> 00:40:52.672
Everywhere we look, if there's an inflammatory lesion there in the liver, the lung,

727
00:40:52.692 --> 00:40:56.232
breast cancer, it's there. And this expresses TNF alpha,

728
00:40:56.412 --> 00:41:00.072
OSM, IL-1 beta, and it basically secretes a bunch of cytokines.

