00:54:46.180 --> 00:54:48.600
receive CAR T cells or something else

971
00:54:49.520 --> 00:54:52.720
and have that therapy be more effective? That's how we're thinking about it.

972
00:54:52.760 --> 00:54:56.000
I would love to get to a point where we had a monotherapy with macrophages.

973
00:54:56.040 --> 00:54:56.050
Mm.

974
00:54:56.050 --> 00:54:59.020
Maybe we'll get there, but initially, I think we have to do this in

975
00:54:59.060 --> 00:55:02.970
combination. And then for brain tumors, the cancer

976
00:55:03.040 --> 00:55:05.440
neuroscience part of this is also important, and it's probably going to end up

977
00:55:05.480 --> 00:55:08.520
being that we do three or four different therapies for these patients.

978
00:55:09.020 --> 00:55:12.660
The question is going to be, how do we do that in sequence to be best for

979
00:55:12.880 --> 00:55:13.260
outcomes?

980
00:55:13.720 --> 00:55:16.540
Okay. Makes sense. I have always have kind of crazy idea.

981
00:55:16.620 --> 00:55:20.040
I was thinking, if you can hijack those kind of myeloid cells in the brain,

